.RE

.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRWhen adding custom metadata, make sure not to use any of the keys mentioned above as that may cause a lot of confusion about the log events.


.PP
Logger merges all the metadata maps before forwarding the log event to the handlers. If the same keys occur, values from the log call overwrite process metadata, which overwrites the primary metadata, which in turn overwrite values set by Logger.

.PP
The following custom metadata keys have special meaning:

domain
.RS 2
The value associated with this key is used by filters for grouping log events originating from, for example, specific functional areas. See 
\fIlogger_filters:domain/2\fR for a description of how this field can be used.

.RE

report_cb
.RS 2
If the log message is specified as a 
\fIreport/0\fR, the \fIreport_cb\fR key can be associated with a fun (report callback) that converts the report to a format string and arguments, or directly to a string. See the type definition of \fIreport_cb/0\fR, and section Log Message in the User's Guide for more information about report callbacks.

.RE


